         <h2>Yavapai</h2>
        <p>The Yavapai is a Native American tribe in the region. Their name translates to "People of the Sun."</p>
        <p>There are four bands of Yavapai, the Western Yavapai, the Northwestern Yavapai, the Southeastern Yavapai and Northeastern Yavapai.</p>
        <p>There are multiple reservations for the Yavapai Tribe, including the Yavapai-Apache Nation Indian Reservation, the Yavapai Prescott Indian Reservation and Fort McDowell Reservation, all in Arizona.</p>
        <p>The Yavapai were often mistaken for the neighboring Apache tribe.</p>
